      "content": "hey, im working on a paper for my linguistics class about how people judge different ways of speaking. i have these two short paragraphs and i want to know which one sounds more \"academic\" or \"intelligent\" if you were reading them in a university setting.\n\nSample A: \"The research findings indicate a significant correlation between socioeconomic status and educational attainment, suggesting that systemic barriers play a crucial role in outcome disparities.\"\n\nSample B: \"The results show how folks' money and how much school they get really tied together, and it's clear that the way things are set up is what's making the gap so big.\"\n\nwhich one comes across as more competent in a professional setting?",
