      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that A is more formal, but isn't the distinction between \"academic\" and \"informal\" basically just a way of centering one specific type of speech? like, if someone uses AAVE or a dialect that isn't standard white middle-class english, are they automatically being judged as less intelligent or less \"competent\" because of how they structure their sentences? even if their actual ideas are just as complex?",
